.TH XCONNECT 1 "July 2026" "2.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xconnect \- KDE Connect protocol daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xconnect
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBxconnect\fR is a background daemon implementing the KDE Connect protocol in Vala and C. It handles TLS-encrypted device pairing, persistent clipboard synchronization, notification mirroring, incoming call notifications with ringer mute controls, and file/URL transfer capabilities over local Wi-Fi.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enables debug logging output.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enables verbose output.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xconnectctl (1)
